y and Pomeroy, who help hide him from Dorothy, who hatches numerous schemes in an attempt to photograph Tommy/Russ being a sailor.","genre_ids":[35,10402,10752],"popularity":0.3859,"vote_count":34,"poster_path":"/5sdXSwjR3Ed6eE6rXdudbpWUH1.jpg","release_date":"1941-05-30","vote_average":6.338,"backdrop_path":"/eoJyPt7me4tpIEu6JQeS240tUPL.jpg","original_title":"In the Navy","original_language":"en"},{"id":33538,"adult":false,"title":"The Noose Hangs High","video":false,"overview":"Two window washers who are mistaken by Nick Craig, a bookie, as the messengers he sent for to pick up $50,000. Now the person he sent them to sent two of his men to get the money back but they found out about it. So they try to mail to Craig but a mix up has the money sent somewhere else and the woman who got it spent it. Now Craig needs the money to pay off one of his clients.","genre_ids":[35],"popularity":0.3968,"vote_count":22,"poster_path":"/gLleQgRllDlxRlTxLFywvsoOpQU.jpg","release_date":"1948-04-05","vote_average":6.8,"backdrop_path":"/zrpKl4x8lulnlr2AFVk8WP2PYqj.jpg","original_title":"The Noose Hangs High","original_language":"en"},{"id":36222,"adult":false,"title":"Dead or Alive: Final","video":false,"overview":"In post-apocalyptic Yokohama, a hard-boiled cop and a mellowed out drifter hook up with a gang of rebels. When the gang kidnap the cop's son, the wheels are set in motion for an inevitable showdown.","genre_ids":[28,35,878,80],"popularity":0.5014,"vote_count":66,"poster_path":"/7wHsgK1dvFdp6pv3ok3BHDY33Op.jpg","release_date":"2002-01-12","vote_average":5.629,"backdrop_path":"/uXCJQ6hEYAPcoV3LuD8m3vZC1OY.jpg","original_title":"DEAD OR ALIVE FINAL","original_language":"ja"}],"external_ids":{"imdb_id":"tt2238032","twitter_id":null,"facebook_id":null,"wikidata_id":"Q18613571","instagram_id":null},"social_ids":{"twitter":null,"facebook":null,"instagram":null},"gdvg_id":148185,"wiki_plot":null,"wiki_synopsis":null,"wiki_episode_guide":null,"wiki_production":null,"wiki_cast_notes"